# Sample HTTP requests for testing the acquireLease endpoint
# Usage: open this file with VS Code and use the REST Client extension, or copy the curl examples.

### Acquire a lease (happy path, with metadata)
POST http://localhost:8080/api/v1/leases
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "owner": "test-user-1",
  "metadata": { "purpose": "integration-test", "requestId": "req-123" }
}

### Acquire another lease (happy path, without metadata)
POST http://localhost:8080/api/v1/leases
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "owner": "test-user-2"
}

### Example: conflict response (when no free schemas)
# The server returns 409 with body: { "error": "no free schemas" }
POST http://localhost:8080/api/v1/leases
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "owner": "exhaust-test"
}

### curl example for the first request
# Run from a terminal:
# curl -v -X POST http://localhost:8080/api/v1/leases -H "Content-Type: application/json" -d "{\"owner\":\"test-user-1\",\"metadata\":{\"purpose\":\"integration-test\"}}"

